{
  "texts": [
    "A similar method has been adopted in the literature [80].",
    "Xiao et al. [4] fused two single-modal trackers via an adaptive weight map.",
    "[78], data from multiple sources are used step-by-step to locate the target.",
    "A rough target position is first estimated by optical flow in the visible domain, and the final result is determined by partbased matching method with RGB-D data.",
    "Pre-processingThe second goal of auxiliary modality is to transform the target into 3D space before target modeling via RGB-D data, using the available depth map."
  ]
}